rticulation within film studies. In using the tradition of aesthetics to illuminate Godard’s late films and videos, Morgan shows that these works transform the basic terms and categories of aesthetics in and for the cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMotion picturesxAesthetics. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  a20th century art.  a20th century film.  aaesthetics in cinema.  abooks for film lovers.  acinema and culture.  acinema history.  acontemporary cinema.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aeducational books.  aengaging.  afamous film producers.  afilm history.  afilm majors.  afilm studies books.  ahistory of cinema production.  ahistory.  ainformative books.  ajean luc godard.  aleisure reads.  amovie and video production.  amovie lovers.  anonfiction reading.  apage turner.  aperforming arts.  asocial cinema.  avideo direction and production.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095396340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953963423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953963/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles